{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"PRO","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Proverbs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Proverbs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Proverbs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Proverbs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Proverbs"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Beginning of Knowledge"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../proverbs/9.htm|>Proverbs 9:1–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"These are the proverbs of Solomon son of David, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["king of Israel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"for gaining wisdom and discipline, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for comprehending words of insight, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"and for receiving instruction in wise living "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and in righteousness, justice, and equity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"To impart prudence to the simple ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered <i>simple</i> in Proverbs refers to one who is naive, without moral direction, or inclined to evil."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and knowledge and discretion to the young, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"let the wise listen and gain instruction, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the discerning acquire wise counsel "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"by understanding the proverbs and parables, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the sayings and riddles of the wise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but fools ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew words rendered as <i>fool</i> in Proverbs denote one who is morally deficient."]}],"caller":"+"},"despise wisdom and discipline. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Enticement of Sin"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Listen, my son, to your father’s instruction, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not forsake  the teaching of your mother. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"For they are a garland of grace on your head "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a pendant around your neck. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"My son, if sinners entice you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not yield to them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"If they say, Come along, let us lie in wait for blood, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["let us ambush the innocent without cause, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"let us swallow them alive like Sheol, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and whole like those descending into the Pit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"We will find all manner of precious goods; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["we will fill our houses with plunder. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Throw in your lot with us; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["let us all share one purse "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"my son, do not walk the road with them "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or set foot upon their path. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"For their feet run to evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and they are swift to shed blood. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"How futile it is to spread the net "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["where any bird  can see it! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But they lie in wait for their own blood; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they ambush their own lives. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Such is the fate of all who are greedy, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whose unjust gain  takes the lives of its possessors. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Wisdom Calls Aloud"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Wisdom calls out in the street, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she lifts her voice in the square; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"in the main concourse ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>from the top of the wall</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"she cries aloud, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at the city  gates she makes her speech: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"How long, O simple ones, will you love your simple ways? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["How long will scoffers delight  in their scorn "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and fools hate knowledge? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"If you had repented at my rebuke, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["then surely I would have poured out my spirit on you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I would have made my words known to you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Because you refused my call, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and no one took my outstretched hand, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"because you neglected all my counsel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and wanted none of my correction, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"in turn I will mock your calamity; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will sneer when terror strikes you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"when your dread comes like a storm, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your destruction  like a whirlwind, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when distress and anguish overwhelm you . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Then they will call on me, but I will not answer; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they will earnestly seek me, but will not find me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," For they hated knowledge "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and chose not to fear the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"They accepted none of my counsel; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they despised all my reproof. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"So they will eat the fruit of their own way, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and be filled with their own devices. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"For the waywardness of the simple will slay them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the complacency of fools will destroy them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"But whoever listens to me will dwell in safety, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["secure from the fear of evil. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Benefits of Wisdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"My son, if you accept my words "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and hide my commandments within you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"if you incline your ear to wisdom "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and direct your heart to understanding, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"if you truly call out to insight "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and lift your voice to understanding, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"if you seek it like silver "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and search it out like hidden treasure, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"then you will discern the fear of the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and discover the knowledge of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"For the LORD gives wisdom; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from His mouth come knowledge and understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"He stores up sound wisdom for the upright; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He is a shield to those who walk with integrity, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"to guard the paths of justice "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and protect the way of His saints. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then you will discern righteousness "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and justice and equity— every good path. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For wisdom will enter your heart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and knowledge will delight your soul. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Discretion will watch over you,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and understanding will guard you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"to deliver you from the way of evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the man who speaks perversity, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"from those who leave the straight paths "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to walk in the ways of darkness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"from those who enjoy doing evil "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and rejoice in the twistedness of evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"whose paths are crooked "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and whose ways are devious. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"It will rescue you from the forbidden woman, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>wayward wife</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the stranger ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>adulteress</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"with seductive words "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"who abandons the partner of her youth  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and forgets the covenant of her God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For her house sinks down to death, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and her tracks to the departed spirits. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>to the Rephaim</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"None who go to her  return "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or negotiate the paths of life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"So you will follow in the ways of the good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and keep to the paths of the righteous. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For the upright will inhabit the land, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the blameless will remain in it; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"but the wicked will be cut off from the land, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the unfaithful will be uprooted. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Trust in the LORD with All Your Heart"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"My son, do not forget my teaching, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but let your heart keep my commandments; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"for they will add length to your days, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["years and peace to your life "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Never let loving devotion ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Forms of the Hebrew <i>chesed</i> are translated here and in most cases throughout the Scriptures as <i>loving devotion</i>; the range of meaning includes <i>love</i>, <i>goodness</i>, <i>kindness</i>, <i>faithfulness</i>, and <i>mercy</i>, as well as <i>loyalty to a covenant</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"or faithfulness leave you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["bind them around your neck, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["write them on the tablet of your heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then you will find favor and high regard  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the sight of God and man. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Trust in the LORD with all your heart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and lean not on your own understanding; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"in all your ways acknowledge Him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and He will make your paths straight. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Be not wise in your own eyes; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["fear  the LORD and turn away from evil. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"This will bring healing to your body ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>navel</i> "]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and refreshment ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>medicine</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"to your bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Honor  the LORD with your wealth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and with the firstfruits of all your crops; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"then your barns will be filled with plenty, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your vats will overflow with new wine. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"My son, do not reject the discipline of the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not loathe His rebuke; ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX <i>and do not lose heart when He rebukes</i>; cited in Hebrews 12:5"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"for  the LORD disciplines the one He loves, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as does a father  the son in whom he delights. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX <i>and He flogs every son He receives</i>; cited in Hebrews 12:6"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Blessings of Wisdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Blessed is the man who finds wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the man who acquires understanding, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"for she is more profitable  than silver, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and her gain is better than fine gold. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"She is more precious than rubies; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["nothing  you desire compares with her. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Long life is in her right hand; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in her left hand are riches and honor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"All her ways  are pleasant, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and all her paths are peaceful. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"She is a tree of life to those who embrace her, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and those who lay hold of her are blessed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The LORD founded the earth by wisdom "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and established the heavens by understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"By His knowledge the watery depths were broken open, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the clouds dripped with dew. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"My son, do not lose sight of this: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Preserve sound judgment and discernment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"They will be life to your soul "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and adornment to your neck. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Then you will go on your way in safety, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your foot will not stumble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"When you lie down, you will not be afraid; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when you rest, your sleep will be sweet. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Do not fear sudden danger "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or the ruin that overtakes the wicked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"for the LORD will be your confidence "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and will keep your foot from the snare. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Do not withhold good from the deserving ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>from its owners</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when it is within your power to act. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Do not tell your neighbor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Come back tomorrow and I will provide” "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when you already have the means . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Do not devise evil against your neighbor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for he trustfully dwells beside you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Do not accuse  a man without cause, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when he has done you no harm. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Do not envy a violent  man "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or choose any of his ways; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"for the LORD detests the perverse , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He is a friend to the upright. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"The curse of the LORD is on the house of the wicked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He blesses the home of the righteous. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"}," He mocks the mockers, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but gives grace to the humble. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:34 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX <i>The Lord opposes the proud, but gives grace to the humble</i>; cited in James 4:6 and 1 Peter 5:5"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"The wise will inherit honor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but fools are held up to shame. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Father’s Instruction"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Listen, my sons, to a father’s instruction; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["pay attention and gain understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"For I give you sound teaching; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not abandon my directive. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"When I was a son to my father, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["tender and the only child of my mother, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"he taught me and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Let your heart lay hold of my words; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["keep my commands and you will live. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Get wisdom, get understanding; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not forget  my words  or turn from them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Do not forsake wisdom, and she will preserve you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["love her, and she will guard you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Wisdom is supreme; so acquire wisdom. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And whatever you may acquire, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>And whatever else you acquire</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"gain understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Prize her, and she will exalt you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["if you embrace her, she will honor you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"She will set a garland of grace on your head; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she will present you with a crown of beauty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Listen, my son, and receive my words, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the years of your life will be many.  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"I will guide you in the way of wisdom; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will lead you on straight paths. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"When you walk, your steps will not be impeded; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when you run, you will not stumble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Hold on to instruction; do not let go. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Guard it, for it is your life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Do not set foot on the path of the wicked "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or walk in the way of evildoers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Avoid it; do not travel on it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Turn from it and pass on by. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"For they cannot sleep "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["unless  they do evil; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they are deprived of slumber "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["until  they make someone fall. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"For they eat the bread of wickedness "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and drink the wine of violence. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The path of the righteous is like the first gleam  of dawn, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["shining brighter and brighter until midday . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"But the way of the wicked is like the darkest gloom; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they do not know what makes them stumble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"My son, pay attention to my words; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["incline your ear to my sayings. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Do not lose sight of them; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["keep them within your heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"For they are life to those who find them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and health to the whole body. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Guard your heart with all diligence, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for from it flow springs of life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Put away deception from your mouth; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["keep  your lips from perverse speech. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Let your eyes look forward; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["fix your gaze straight ahead. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Make a level path for your feet, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Ponder the path for your feet</i>; LXX <i>Make straight paths for your feet</i>; cited in Hebrews 12:13"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and all your ways will be sure. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Do not swerve to the right or to the left; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["turn your feet away from evil. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Avoiding Immorality"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../leviticus/20.htm#10|>Leviticus 20:10–21</a>; <a href =|../1_corinthians/5.htm|>1 Corinthians 5:1–8</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"My son, pay attention to my wisdom; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["incline your ear to my insight, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"that you may maintain discretion "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your lips may preserve knowledge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Though the lips of the forbidden woman ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the adulteress</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"drip honey "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and her speech ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>her palate</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"is smoother than oil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"in the end she is bitter as wormwood, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["sharp as a double-edged sword. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Her feet go down to death; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["her steps lead straight to Sheol. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>lay hold of Sheol</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"She does not consider the path of life; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she does not know that her ways are unstable. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So now, my sons, listen to me, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not turn aside from the words of my mouth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Keep your path far from her; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not go near  the door of her house, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"lest you concede your vigor to others, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your years to one who is cruel; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"lest strangers feast on your wealth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your labors enrich the house of a foreigner. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"At the end of your life you will groan "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when your flesh and your body are spent, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"and you will say, How I hated discipline, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and my heart despised reproof! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"I did not listen to the voice of my teachers "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or incline my ear to my mentors. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I am on the brink of utter ruin "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the midst of the whole assembly . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Drink water from your own cistern, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and running water from your own well. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Why should your springs flow in the streets, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["your streams of water in the public squares? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Let them be yours alone, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["never to be shared with strangers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"May your fountain be blessed, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and may you rejoice in the wife of your youth: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"A loving doe, a graceful fawn— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["may her breasts satisfy you always ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["may you be captivated ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>be led astray</i>; also in verse 20"]}],"caller":"+"},"by her love forever. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Why be captivated, my son, by an adulteress, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or embrace the bosom of a stranger? ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>a foreign woman</i> or <i>another man’s wife</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For a man’s ways are before the eyes of the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the LORD examines ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>ponders</i> or <i>makes level</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"all his paths. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The iniquities of a wicked man entrap him;  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the cords of his sin entangle him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"He dies for lack of discipline, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["led astray by his own great folly. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Warnings against Foolishness"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"My son, if you have put up security for your neighbor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["if you have struck hands in pledge  with a stranger, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"if you have been trapped by the words of your lips, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["ensnared by the words of your mouth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"then do this, my son, to free yourself, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you have fallen into your neighbor’s hands: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Go, humble yourself, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>hasten</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and press your plea with your neighbor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Allow no sleep to your eyes "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or slumber to your eyelids. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Free yourself, like a gazelle from the hand of the hunter, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew does not include <i>of the hunter</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a bird from the snare of the fowler. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Walk in the manner of  the ant, O slacker; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["observe its ways and become wise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," Without a commander, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["without an overseer or ruler, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"it prepares its provisions in summer; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it gathers its food at harvest. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"How long will you lie there, O slacker? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When will you get up from your sleep? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"A little sleep, a little slumber, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a little folding of the hands to rest, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and poverty will come upon you like a robber, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and need like a bandit . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"A worthless person, a wicked man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["walks with a perverse mouth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"winking his eyes, speaking with his feet, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and pointing with his fingers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"With deceit in his heart he devises evil; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he continually  sows discord. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Therefore  calamity will come upon him suddenly; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in an instant he will be shattered beyond recovery. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"There are six things that the LORD hates, seven that are detestable to Him: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"haughty eyes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a lying tongue, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["hands that shed innocent blood, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"a heart that devises wicked schemes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["feet that run swiftly to evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"a false witness who gives false testimony, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and one who stirs up discord among brothers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Warnings against Adultery"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"My son, keep your father’s commandment, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not forsake your mother’s teaching. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Bind them always upon your heart; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["tie them around your neck. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"When you walk, they will guide you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when you lie down, they will watch over you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when you awake, they will speak to you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"For this commandment is a lamp, this teaching is a light, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the reproofs of discipline are the way to life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"to keep you from the evil woman, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the smooth tongue of the adulteress. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the stranger</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Do not lust in your heart  for her beauty "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or let her captivate you with her eyes. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:25 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>eyelids</i> or <i>eyelashes</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"For the levy  of the prostitute is poverty , ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>a crust of bread</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}," "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the adulteress  preys upon your very life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Can a man embrace  fire "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and his clothes not be burned? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Can a man walk on hot coals "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["without scorching his feet? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"So is he who sleeps with  another man’s wife; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["no one  who touches her will go unpunished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Men do not despise the thief "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["if he steals to satisfy his  hunger. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Yet if caught, he must pay sevenfold ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he must give up all the wealth of his house. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"He who commits adultery  lacks judgment; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whoever does so destroys himself. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Wounds and dishonor will befall him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and his reproach will never be wiped away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"For jealousy enrages a husband , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he will show no mercy in the day of vengeance. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"He will not be appeased  by any ransom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or persuaded  by lavish gifts. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Warnings about the Adulteress"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"My son, keep my words "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and treasure my commandments within you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Keep my commandments and live; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["guard my teachings as the apple ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>the pupil</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"of your eye. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Tie them to your fingers; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["write them on the tablet of your heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Say to wisdom, You are my sister, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and call understanding your kinsman, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"that they may keep you from the adulteress , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the stranger with seductive words. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"For at the window of my house "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I looked through the lattice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I saw among the simple, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I noticed among the youths, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a young man lacking judgment, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"crossing the street near her corner, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["strolling down the road to her house, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"at twilight, as the day was fading  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["into the dark of the night . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then a woman came out to meet him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with the attire of a harlot and cunning of heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"She is loud and defiant; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["her feet do not remain at home. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Now in the street, now in the squares, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she lurks at every corner. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"She seizes him and kisses him; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she brazenly  says to him: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I have made my peace  offerings; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["today I have paid my vows. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"So  I came out to meet you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I sought you,  and I have found you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"I have decked my bed with coverings, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with colored linen from Egypt. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with aloes, and with cinnamon. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Come, let us take our fill of love till morning. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Let us delight in loving caresses! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"For my husband is not at home; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he has gone on a long journey. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"He took with him a bag of money "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and will not return  till the moon is full. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"With her great persuasion she entices him; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with her flattering lips she lures him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"He follows her  on impulse, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like an ox going to the slaughter, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a deer bounding into a trap, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Probable reading (see LXX, Vulgate, Syriac); Hebrew <i>like fetters to discipline a fool</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"until an arrow pierces his liver, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a bird darting into a snare— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["not knowing  it will cost him his life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Now, my sons, listen to me, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and attend to the words of my mouth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not stray into her paths. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"For she has brought many down to death; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["her slain are many in number. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Her house is the road to Sheol, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["descending to the chambers of death. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Excellence of Wisdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Does not wisdom call out, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and understanding raise her voice? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"On the heights  overlooking the road, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at the crossroads  she takes her stand. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Beside the gates to the city, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at the entrances  she cries out: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"To you, O men, I call out, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and my cry is to the sons of men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"O simple ones, learn to be shrewd; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["O fools, gain understanding . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>instruct your minds</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Listen, for I speak of noble things, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the opening of my lips will reveal right. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"For my mouth will speak the truth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and wickedness is detestable to my lips. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"All the words of my mouth are righteous; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["none are crooked or perverse. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"They are all plain to the discerning, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and upright to those who find knowledge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Receive my instruction instead of silver, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and knowledge rather than pure gold. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For wisdom is more precious than rubies, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and nothing  you desire compares with her. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I, wisdom, dwell together with prudence, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and I find knowledge and discretion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"To fear the LORD is to hate evil; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I hate arrogant pride, evil conduct, and perverse speech. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Counsel and sound judgment are mine; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I have insight and strength. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"By me kings reign, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and rulers enact just laws; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"By me princes rule, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and all nobles who govern justly. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some Hebrew manuscripts and LXX <i>who govern the earth</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"I love those who love me, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and those who seek me early shall find me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"With me are riches and honor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["enduring wealth and righteousness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"My fruit is better than gold, pure gold, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and my harvest surpasses choice silver. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"I walk in the way of righteousness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["along the paths of justice, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"bestowing wealth on those who love me "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and making their treasuries full. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The LORD created me as His first course, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>The LORD possessed me at the beginning of His way</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["before His works of old. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"From everlasting I was established, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the beginning, before the earth began. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"When there were no watery depths, I was brought forth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when no springs were overflowing with water. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Before the mountains were settled, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["before the hills, I was brought forth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"before  He made the land or fields, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or any of the dust of the earth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"I was there when He established the heavens, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when He inscribed a circle on the face of the deep, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"when He established the clouds above, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when the fountains of the deep gushed forth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"when He set a boundary for the sea, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so that the waters would not surpass His command, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when He marked out the foundations of the earth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Then I was a skilled craftsman at His side, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and His delight ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>filled with His delight</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"day by day, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["rejoicing always  in His presence. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"I was rejoicing in His whole world , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["delighting together in the sons of men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Now therefore, my sons, listen to me, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for blessed are those who keep my ways. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Listen to instruction and be wise; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not ignore it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Blessed is the man who listens to me, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["watching daily  at my doors, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["waiting at the posts of my doorway. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"For whoever finds me finds life "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and obtains the favor of the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"But he who fails to find me harms himself; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["all who hate me love death. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Way of Wisdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../proverbs/1.htm|>Proverbs 1:1–7</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Wisdom has built her house; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she has carved out ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; LXX, Syriac, and Aramaic Targum <i>has set up</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"her seven pillars. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"She has prepared her meat and mixed her wine; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she has also set her table. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"She has sent out her maidservants; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she calls out from  the heights of the city. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Whoever is simple, let him turn in here! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she says to him who lacks judgment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Come, eat my bread "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and drink the wine I have mixed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Leave your folly behind, and you will live; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["walk in the way of understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"He who corrects a mocker brings shame on himself; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he who rebukes a wicked man taints himself. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Do not rebuke a mocker, or he will hate you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["rebuke a wise man, and he will love you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Instruct a wise man, and he will be wiser still; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["teach a righteous man, and he will increase his learning. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and knowledge of the Holy One is understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For through wisdom ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX, Syriac, and Aramaic Targum; Hebrew <i>through me</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"your days will be multiplied, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and years will be added to your life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"If you are wise, you are wise to your own advantage; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but if you scoff, you alone will bear the consequences. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Way of Folly"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"The woman named Folly is loud; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she is naive and knows nothing . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"She sits at the door of her house, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["on a seat in the heights of the city, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"calling out to those who pass by,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who make their paths straight. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Whoever is simple, let him turn in here! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she says to him who lacks judgment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Stolen water is sweet, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and bread eaten in secret is tasty! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But they do not know that the dead ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>the Rephaim</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"are there, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that her guests are in the depths of Sheol. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Solomon’s Proverbs: The Wise Son"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"The proverbs of Solomon: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["A wise son brings joy to his father, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a foolish son grief to his mother. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Ill-gotten treasures profit nothing, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but righteousness brings deliverance from death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The LORD  does not let the righteous go hungry, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He denies the craving of the wicked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Idle hands make one poor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but diligent hands bring wealth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"He who gathers in summer is a wise son, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who sleeps during harvest is a disgraceful son. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Blessings are on the head of the righteous, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the mouth of the wicked conceals violence. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>but violence covers the mouth of the wicked</i>; also in verse 11"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The memory of the righteous is a blessing, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the name of the wicked will rot. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"A wise heart will receive commandments, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but foolish lips will come to ruin. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"He who walks in integrity walks securely, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who perverts his ways will be found out. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"He who winks the eye causes grief, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and foolish lips will come to ruin. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>babbling fools will fall</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"The mouth of the righteous is a fountain of life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the mouth of the wicked conceals violence. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Hatred stirs up dissension , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but love covers all transgressions. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See 1 Peter 4:8"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Wisdom is found on the lips of the discerning, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a rod is for the back of him who lacks judgment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The wise store up knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the mouth of the fool invites destruction. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The wealth of the rich man is his fortified city, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but poverty is the ruin of the poor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The labor of the righteous leads to life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the gain of the wicked brings punishment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Whoever heeds instruction is on the path to life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who ignores reproof goes astray. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The one who conceals hatred has lying lips, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and whoever spreads slander  is a fool. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"When words are many, sin is unavoidable , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who restrains his lips is wise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"The tongue of the righteous is choice silver, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the heart of the wicked has little worth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"The lips of the righteous feed many, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but fools die for lack of judgment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The blessing of the LORD  enriches, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and He adds no sorrow to it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"The fool delights in shameful conduct, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man of understanding has wisdom. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"What the wicked man  dreads will overtake him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the desire of the righteous will be granted. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"When the whirlwind passes, the wicked are no more, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the righteous are secure forever. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Like vinegar to the teeth and smoke to the eyes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so is the slacker to those who send him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"The fear of the LORD prolongs life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the years of the wicked will be cut short. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"The hope of the righteous is joy, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the expectations of the wicked will perish. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"The way of the LORD is a refuge to the upright, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but destruction awaits those who do evil. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"The righteous will never  be shaken, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the wicked will not inhabit the land. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"The mouth of the righteous brings forth wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a perverse tongue will be cut out. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"The lips of the righteous know what is fitting, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the mouth of the wicked is perverse. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Dishonest Scales"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../deuteronomy/25.htm#13|>Deuteronomy 25:13–16</a>; <a href =|../ezekiel/45.htm#10|>Ezekiel 45:10–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Dishonest scales are an abomination to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but an accurate weight is His delight. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"When pride comes, disgrace follows, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but with humility comes wisdom. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The integrity of the upright guides them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the perversity of the faithless destroys them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Riches  are worthless in the day of wrath, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but righteousness brings deliverance from death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The righteousness of the blameless directs their path, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the wicked fall by their own wickedness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"The righteousness of the upright delivers them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the faithless are trapped by their own desires. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"When the wicked man dies, his hope perishes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the hope of his strength vanishes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The righteous man is delivered from trouble; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in his place the wicked man goes in. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"With his mouth the ungodly man destroys his neighbor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but through knowledge the righteous are rescued. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"When the righteous thrive, the city rejoices, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and when the wicked perish, there are shouts of joy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"By the blessing of the upright a city is built up, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but by the mouth of the wicked it is torn down. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Whoever shows contempt for his neighbor lacks judgment, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man of understanding remains silent. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"A gossip  reveals a secret, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a trustworthy person keeps a confidence. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"For lack of guidance, a nation falls, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but with many counselors comes deliverance. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"}," He who puts up security for a stranger will surely suffer , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the one who hates indebtedness is secure. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"A gracious woman attains honor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but ruthless men gain only wealth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"A kind man benefits himself, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a cruel man brings trouble on himself. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The wicked man earns an empty wage, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who sows righteousness reaps a true reward. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Genuine righteousness leads to life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the pursuit of evil brings death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"The perverse in heart are an abomination to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the blameless in their walk are His delight. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Be assured  that the wicked will not go unpunished, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the offspring of the righteous will escape. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Like a gold ring in a pig’s snout "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a beautiful woman who lacks discretion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"The desire of the righteous leads only to good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the hope of the wicked brings wrath. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"}," One gives freely, yet gains even more; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["another withholds what is right, only to become poor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"A generous soul will prosper, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who refreshes others  will himself be refreshed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"The people will curse the hoarder of grain, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but blessing will crown the one who sells it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"He who searches out good finds favor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but evil will come to him who seeks it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"He who trusts in his riches  will fall, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the righteous will thrive like foliage. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"He who brings trouble on his house will inherit the wind, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the fool will be servant to the wise of heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who wins souls is wise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"If the righteous receive their due on earth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["how much more  the ungodly and the sinner! ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX <i>If it is hard for the righteous to be saved, what will become of the ungodly and the sinner?</i> Cited in 1 Peter 4:18"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Loving Discipline and Knowledge"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Whoever loves discipline loves knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who hates correction is stupid. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The good man obtains favor from the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the LORD condemns a man who devises evil. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A man cannot be established through wickedness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the righteous cannot be uprooted . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"A wife of noble character is her husband’s crown, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but she who causes shame is like decay in his bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The plans of the righteous are just, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the counsel of the wicked leads to deceit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"The words of the wicked lie in wait for blood, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the speech of the upright rescues them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The wicked are overthrown and perish, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the house of the righteous will stand. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"A man is praised according to his wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a twisted mind is despised. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Better to be lightly esteemed yet have a servant "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than to be self-important but lack food. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"A righteous man regards the life of his animal, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the tender mercies of the wicked are only cruelty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"The one who works his land will have plenty of food, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever chases fantasies lacks judgment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The wicked desire the plunder of evil men, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the root of the righteous flourishes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"An evil man is trapped by his rebellious speech, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a righteous man escapes from trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"By fruitful speech a man is filled with good things, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the work of his hands returns to him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The way of a fool is right in his own eyes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a wise man listens to counsel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"A fool’s anger is known at once, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a prudent man overlooks an insult. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"He who speaks the truth declares what is right, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a false witness speaks deceit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," Speaking rashly is like a piercing sword, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the tongue of the wise brings healing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Truthful lips endure forever , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a lying tongue lasts only a moment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Deceit is in the hearts of those who devise evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the counselors of peace have joy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"No harm befalls the righteous , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the wicked are filled with trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Lying lips are detestable to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but those who deal faithfully are His delight. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"A shrewd man keeps his knowledge to himself, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a foolish heart proclaims its folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The hand of the diligent will rule, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but laziness ends in forced labor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Anxiety weighs down the heart of a man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a good word cheers it up. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"A righteous man is cautious in friendship, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the ways of the wicked lead them astray. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"A lazy man does not roast his game, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a diligent man prizes his possession. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"There is life in the path of righteousness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but another path   leads to death. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Father’s Discipline"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"A wise son heeds his father’s discipline, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a mocker does not listen to rebuke. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"From the fruit of his lips a man enjoys good things, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the desire of the faithless is violence. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"He who guards his mouth protects his life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the one who opens his lips invites his own ruin "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The slacker  craves yet has nothing, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the soul of the diligent is fully satisfied. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The righteous hate falsehood , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the wicked bring shame and disgrace. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Righteousness guards the man of integrity , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but wickedness undermines the sinner. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," One pretends to be rich, but has nothing ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["another pretends to be poor, yet has great wealth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Riches may ransom a man’s life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a poor man hears no threat. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The light of the righteous shines brightly, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the lamp of the wicked is extinguished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Arrogance leads only to strife, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but wisdom is with the well-advised. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Dishonest wealth will dwindle, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but what is earned through hard work will be multiplied. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Hope deferred makes the heart sick, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but desire fulfilled is a tree of life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"He who despises instruction will pay the penalty "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the one who respects a command  will be rewarded. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The teaching ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>law</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"of the wise is a fountain of life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["turning one from the snares of death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Good understanding wins favor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the way of the faithless is difficult. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Every prudent man acts with knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a fool displays his folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"A wicked messenger falls into trouble, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a faithful envoy brings healing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Poverty and shame come to him who ignores discipline, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever heeds correction is honored. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Desire fulfilled is sweet to the soul, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but turning from evil is detestable to fools. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"He who walks with the wise will become wise, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the companion of fools will be destroyed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Disaster  pursues sinners, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but prosperity is the reward of the righteous. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"A good man leaves an inheritance to his children’s children, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the sinner’s wealth is passed to the righteous. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Abundant food is in the fallow ground of the poor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but without justice it is swept away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"He who spares the rod hates his son, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who loves him disciplines him diligently. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"A righteous man eats to his heart’s content, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the stomach of the wicked is empty. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Wise Woman"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Every wise woman builds her house, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a foolish one tears it down with her own hands. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"He who walks in uprightness fears the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the one who is devious in his ways despises Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The proud speech of a fool brings a rod to his back, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the lips of the wise protect them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Where there are no oxen, the manger is empty, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but an abundant harvest comes through the strength of the ox. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"An honest witness does not deceive, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a dishonest witness pours forth lies. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"A mocker seeks wisdom and finds none, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but knowledge comes easily to the discerning. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Stay away from a foolish man; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you will gain no knowledge from his speech. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The wisdom of the prudent is to discern his way, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the folly of fools deceives them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Fools mock the making of amends, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but goodwill is found among the upright. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"The heart knows its own bitterness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and no stranger shares in its joy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"The house of the wicked will be destroyed, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the tent of the upright will flourish. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"There is a way that seems right to a man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but its end is the way of death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Even in laughter the heart may ache, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and joy may end in sorrow. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The backslider in heart receives the fill of his own ways, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a good man is rewarded for his ways. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The simple man believes every word, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the prudent man watches his steps. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"A wise man fears ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>fears the LORD</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and turns from evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a fool is careless and reckless. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"A quick-tempered man  acts foolishly, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a devious man is hated. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The simple inherit folly, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the prudent are crowned with knowledge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The evil bow before the good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the wicked at the gates of the righteous. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"The poor man is hated even by his neighbor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but many are those who love the rich. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"He who despises his neighbor sins, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but blessed is he who shows kindness to the poor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Do not those who contrive evil go astray? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But those who plan goodness find ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>show</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"loving devotion and faithfulness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"There is profit in all labor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but mere talk  leads only to poverty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The crown of the wise is their wealth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the effort of fools is folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"A truthful witness saves lives, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but one who utters lies is deceitful. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"He who fears the LORD is secure in confidence, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and his children shall have a place of refuge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"The fear of the LORD is a fountain of life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["turning a man from the snares of death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"A large population is a king’s splendor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a lack of subjects is a prince’s ruin. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"A patient man  has great understanding, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a quick-tempered man  promotes folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"A tranquil heart is life to the body, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but envy rots the bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Whoever oppresses the poor taunts their Maker, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever is kind to the needy honors Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"The wicked man is thrown down by his own sin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the righteous man has a refuge even in death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Wisdom rests in the heart of the discerning; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even among fools she is known. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:33 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; LXX and Syriac <i>but among fools she is not known</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Righteousness exalts a nation, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but sin is a disgrace to any people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"A king delights in a wise servant, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but his anger falls on the shameful. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Gentle Answer Turns Away Wrath"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"A gentle answer turns away wrath, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a harsh word stirs up anger. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The tongue of the wise commends knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the mouth of the fool spouts folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The eyes of the LORD are in every place, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["observing the evil and the good. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"A soothing tongue is a tree of life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a perverse tongue crushes the spirit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"A fool rejects his father’s discipline, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever heeds correction is prudent. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"The house of the righteous has great treasure, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the income of the wicked is trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The lips of the wise spread knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but not so the hearts of fools. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The sacrifice of the wicked is detestable to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the prayer of the upright is His delight. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The LORD detests the way of the wicked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He loves those who pursue righteousness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Discipline is harsh for him who leaves the path; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he who hates correction will die. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Sheol and Abaddon ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Death and Destruction</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"lie open before the LORD— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["how much more  the hearts  of men! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"A mocker does not love to be reproved, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["nor will he  consult  the wise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"A joyful heart makes a cheerful countenance, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but sorrow of the heart crushes the spirit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"A discerning heart seeks knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the mouth of a fool feeds on folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"All the days of the oppressed are bad, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a cheerful heart has a continual feast. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Better a little with the fear of the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than great treasure with turmoil "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Better a dish of vegetables where there is love "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than a fattened ox with hatred "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"A hot-tempered man stirs up strife, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who is slow to anger calms dispute. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The way of the slacker is like a hedge of thorns, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the path of the upright is a highway. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"A wise son brings joy to his father, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a foolish man despises his mother. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Folly is joy to one who lacks judgment, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man of understanding walks a straight path. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Plans fail for lack of counsel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but with many advisers they succeed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"A man takes joy in a fitting reply  —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and how good is a timely word! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The path of life leads upward for the wise, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that he may avoid going down to Sheol. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"The LORD tears down the house of the proud, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He protects the boundaries of the widow. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"The LORD detests the thoughts of the wicked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the words of the pure are pleasant to Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"He who is greedy for unjust gain brings trouble on his household, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who hates bribes will live. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"The heart of the righteous ponders how to answer, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the mouth of the wicked blurts out evil. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"The LORD is far from the wicked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He hears the prayer of the righteous. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"The light of the eyes cheers the heart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and good news nourishes the bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"}," He who listens to life-giving reproof "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will dwell among the wise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"He who ignores discipline despises himself, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever heeds correction gains understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"The fear of the LORD is the instruction of wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and humility comes before honor. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Reply of the Tongue Is from the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"The plans of the heart belong to man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the reply of the tongue is from the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"All a man’s ways are pure in his own eyes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but his motives are weighed out by the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Commit your works to the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your plans will be achieved. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The LORD has made everything for His purpose— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even the wicked for the day of disaster. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Everyone who is proud in heart is detestable to the LORD; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["be assured that  he will not go unpunished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"By loving devotion and faithfulness iniquity is atoned for, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and by the fear of the LORD one turns aside from evil. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"When a man’s ways please the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He makes even the man’s enemies live at peace with him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Better a little with righteousness "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than great gain with injustice . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"A man’s heart plans his course, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the LORD determines his steps. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"A divine verdict is on the lips of a king; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["his mouth must not betray justice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Honest scales and balances are from the LORD; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["all the weights in the bag are His concern. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Wicked behavior is detestable for kings, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for a throne is established through righteousness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Righteous lips are a king’s delight, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who speaks honestly is beloved. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The wrath of a king is a messenger of death, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a wise man will pacify it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"When a king’s face brightens, there is life; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["his favor is like a rain cloud in spring. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"How much better to acquire wisdom than gold! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["To gain understanding is more desirable than silver. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"The highway of the upright leads away from evil; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he who guards his way protects his life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Pride goes before destruction, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a haughty spirit before a fall. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"It is better to be lowly in spirit among the humble "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than to divide the spoil with the proud. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Whoever heeds  instruction will find success, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Whoever speaks prudently will find what is good</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and blessed is he who trusts in the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"The wise in heart are called discerning, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and pleasant speech promotes instruction. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Understanding is a fountain of life to its possessor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the discipline of fools is folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"The heart of the wise man instructs his mouth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and adds persuasiveness to his lips. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Pleasant words are a honeycomb , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["sweet to the soul and healing to the bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"There is a way that seems right to a man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but its end is the way of death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"A worker’s appetite works for him "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because his hunger drives him onward. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"A worthless man digs up evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" and his speech ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>and what is on his lips</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"is like a scorching fire. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"A perverse man spreads dissension, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a gossip divides close friends. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"A violent man entices his neighbor "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and leads him down a path that is not good. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"He who winks his eye devises perversity; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he who purses his lips is bent on evil. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Gray hair is a crown of glory; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it is attained along the path of righteousness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"He who is slow to anger is better than a warrior, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who controls his temper is greater than one who captures a city. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"The lot is cast  into the lap, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but its every decision is from the LORD. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Better a Dry Morsel in Quietness"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Better a dry morsel in quietness "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than a house full of feasting ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>sacrifices</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"with strife. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"A wise servant will rule over a disgraceful son "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and share his inheritance as one of the brothers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A crucible for silver and a furnace for gold, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the LORD is the tester of hearts. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"A wicked man listens to evil lips; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a liar gives ear to a destructive tongue. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"He who mocks the poor insults their Maker; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whoever gloats over calamity will not go unpunished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Grandchildren  are the crown of the aged, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the glory of a son is his father. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Eloquent words are unfit  for a fool; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["how much worse  are lying lips to a ruler! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"A bribe is a charm  to its giver; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["wherever   he turns, he succeeds. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Whoever conceals an offense promotes love, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who brings it up  separates friends. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"A rebuke cuts into a man of discernment "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["deeper than a hundred lashes cut into a fool. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"An evil man seeks only rebellion; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a cruel messenger will be sent against him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"It is better to meet a bear robbed of her cubs "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than a fool in his folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"If anyone returns evil for good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["evil will never leave his house. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"To start a quarrel is to release a flood; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so abandon the dispute before it breaks out. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Acquitting the guilty and condemning the righteous— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["both are detestable to the LORD . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Why  should the fool have money in his hand "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with no intention of buying wisdom? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"A friend loves at all times, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a brother is born for adversity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"A man lacking judgment strikes hands in pledge "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and puts up security  for his neighbor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"He who loves transgression loves strife; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he who builds his gate high invites destruction. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"The one with a perverse heart finds no good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he whose tongue is deceitful falls into trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"A man fathers a fool to his own grief "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the father of a fool has no joy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"A joyful heart is good medicine, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a broken spirit dries up the bones. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"A wicked man takes a covert bribe ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>a bribe from the bosom</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to subvert the course of justice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Wisdom  is the focus of the discerning, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the eyes of a fool wander to the ends of the earth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"A foolish son brings grief to his father "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and bitterness to her who bore him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"It is surely not good to punish the innocent "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or to flog a noble for his honesty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"A man of knowledge  restrains his words, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a man of understanding maintains a calm spirit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Even a fool is considered wise if he keeps silent, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and discerning when he holds his tongue. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Selfishness of the Unfriendly"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"He who isolates himself pursues selfish desires; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he rebels against all sound judgment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"A fool does not delight in understanding, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but only  in airing his opinions. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"With a wicked man comes contempt as well , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and shame is accompanied by disgrace. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The words of a man’s mouth are deep waters; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the fountain of wisdom is a bubbling brook. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Showing partiality  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>Lifting the face</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"to the wicked is not good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["nor is depriving the innocent of justice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"A fool’s lips bring him strife, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and his mouth invites a beating. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"A fool’s mouth is his ruin "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and his lips are a snare to his soul. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The words of a gossip are like choice morsels "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that go down into the inmost being . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Whoever is slothful in his work "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is brother  to him who destroys. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"The name of the LORD is a strong tower; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the righteous run to it ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>to Him</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and are safe. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"A rich man’s wealth is his fortified city; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it is like a high wall in his imagination. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Before his downfall a man’s heart is proud, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but humility comes before honor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"He who answers a matter before he hears it— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["this is folly and disgrace to him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The spirit of a man can endure his sickness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but who can survive a broken spirit? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The heart of the discerning acquires knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the ear of the wise seeks it out. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"A man’s gift opens doors for him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and brings him before great men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"The first to state his case seems right "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["until another comes and cross-examines him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Casting the lot  ends quarrels "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and separates strong opponents. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"An offended brother is harder to win than a fortified city, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and disputes are like the bars of a castle. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"From the fruit of his mouth a man’s belly is filled; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with the harvest from his lips he is satisfied. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Life and death are in the power of the tongue, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and those who love it will eat its fruit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"He who finds a wife finds a good thing "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and obtains favor from the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"The poor man pleads for mercy , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the rich man answers harshly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"A man of many companions may come to ruin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but there is a friend who stays closer than a brother. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Man of Integrity"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Better a poor man who walks with integrity  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than a fool whose lips are perverse. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Even zeal is no good without knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who hurries his footsteps misses the mark. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A man’s own folly subverts his way, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["yet his heart rages against the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Wealth attracts many friends, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a poor man is deserted by his friend. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"A false witness will not go unpunished, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and one who utters lies will not escape. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Many seek the favor of the prince, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and everyone is a friend of the gift giver. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"All the brothers of a poor man hate him —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["how much more  do his friends avoid him! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He may pursue them with pleading, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but they are nowhere to be found. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"He who acquires wisdom loves himself; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["one who safeguards understanding will find success. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"A false witness will not go unpunished, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and one who pours out lies will perish. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Luxury  is unseemly for a fool— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["how much worse  for a slave to rule over princes! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"A man’s insight gives him patience , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and his virtue is to overlook  an offense. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"A king’s rage is like the roar of a lion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but his favor is like dew on the grass. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"A foolish son is his father’s ruin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a quarrelsome wife is like a constant dripping. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Houses and wealth are inherited from fathers, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a prudent wife is from the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Laziness brings on deep sleep, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and an idle soul will suffer hunger. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"He who keeps a commandment preserves his soul, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who is careless in his ways will die. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Kindness to the poor  is a loan to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and He will repay the lender. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Discipline your son, for in that there is hope; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not be party  to his death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"A man of great anger  must pay the penalty;  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["if you rescue him,  you will have to do so again. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Listen to counsel and accept discipline, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that you may be wise the rest of your days. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Many plans are in a man’s heart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the purpose  of the LORD will prevail. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The desire of a man is loving devotion; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["better to be poor than a liar. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"The fear of the LORD leads to life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that one may rest content, without visitation from harm. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The slacker buries his hand in the dish; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he will not even bring it back to his mouth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Strike a mocker, and the simple will beware; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["rebuke the discerning man, and he will gain knowledge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"He who assaults his father or evicts his mother "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a son who brings shame and disgrace. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"If you cease to hear instruction, my son, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you will stray from the words of knowledge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"A corrupt witness mocks justice, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a wicked mouth swallows iniquity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Judgments are prepared for mockers, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and beatings for the backs of fools. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Wine Is a Mocker"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Wine is a mocker, strong drink is a brawler, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and whoever is led astray by them is not wise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The terror of a king is like the roar of a lion; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whoever provokes him forfeits his own life. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>sins against his own soul</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"It is honorable for a man to resolve a dispute, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but any fool will quarrel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The slacker does not plow in season; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at harvest time he looks, but nothing is there. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The intentions of a man’s heart are deep waters, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man of understanding draws them out. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Many a man proclaims his loving devotion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but who can find a trustworthy man? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The righteous man walks with integrity; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["blessed are his children after him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"A king who sits on a throne to judge "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["sifts out all evil with his eyes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Who can say, I have kept my heart pure; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I am cleansed from my sin”? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Differing weights and unequal measures  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>A stone and a stone, an ephah and an ephah</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["both are detestable to the LORD . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Even a young man is known by his actions— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whether his conduct is pure  and upright. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Ears that hear and eyes that see— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the LORD has made them  both. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Do not love sleep, or you will grow poor; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["open your eyes, and you will have plenty of food. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Worthless, worthless! says the buyer, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but on the way out  he gloats. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"There is an abundance of gold and rubies, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but lips of knowledge are a rare treasure. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Take the garment of the one who posts security for a stranger; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["get collateral if it is for a foreigner. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>a wayward woman</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Food gained by fraud is sweet to a man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but later his mouth is full of gravel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Set plans by consultation, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and wage war under sound guidance. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"He who reveals secrets is a constant gossip; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" avoid the one who babbles ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the one who is simple</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"with his lips. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Whoever curses his father or mother, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["his lamp will be extinguished in deepest darkness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"An inheritance gained quickly "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will not be blessed in the end. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Do not say, I will avenge this evil! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Wait on the LORD, and He will save you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Unequal weights  are detestable to the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and dishonest scales are no good. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"A man’s steps are from the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so how can anyone understand his own way? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"It is a trap for a man to dedicate something rashly, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["only later to reconsider his vows. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"A wise king separates out the wicked "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and drives the threshing wheel over them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"The spirit ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>breath</i> or <i>speech</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"of a man is the lamp of the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["searching out  his inmost being . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Loving devotion and faithfulness preserve a king; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["by these he maintains his throne. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"The glory of young men is their strength, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and gray hair is the splendor of the old. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Lashes and wounds scour evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and beatings cleanse the inmost parts . "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The King’s Heart"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../psalms/21.htm|>Psalm 21:1–13</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"The king’s heart is a waterway  in the hand of the LORD; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He directs it where   He pleases. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"All a man’s ways seem right to him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the LORD weighs the heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"To do righteousness and justice "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is more desirable to the LORD than sacrifice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Haughty eyes and a proud heart— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the guides of the wicked— are sin. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The plans of the diligent  bring plenty, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as surely as haste leads to poverty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Making a fortune by a lying tongue "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a vanishing mist, a deadly pursuit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The violence of the wicked will sweep them away "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because they refuse to do what is just. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The way of a guilty man is crooked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the conduct of the innocent is upright. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Better to live on a corner of the roof "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than to share a house with a quarrelsome wife. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"The soul of the wicked man craves evil; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["his neighbor finds no favor  in his eyes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"When a mocker is punished, the simple gain wisdom; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and when a wise man is instructed, he acquires knowledge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The Righteous One ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>The righteous one</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"considers the house of the wicked "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and brings the wicked to ruin. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Whoever shuts his ears to the cry of the poor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he too shall cry out  and receive no answer. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"A gift in secret soothes anger, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a covert bribe ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>a bribe in the bosom</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"pacifies great wrath. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Justice executed is a joy to the righteous, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a terror to the workers of iniquity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The man who strays from the path of understanding "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will rest in the assembly of the dead. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"He who loves pleasure will become poor ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the one who loves wine and oil will never be rich. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The wicked become a ransom for the righteous, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the faithless for the upright. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Better to live in the desert  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than with a contentious and ill-tempered wife. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Precious treasures and oil are in the dwelling of the wise, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a foolish man consumes them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"He who pursues righteousness and loving devotion "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["finds life, righteousness, and honor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"A wise man scales the city of the mighty "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and pulls down the stronghold in which they trust. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"He who guards his mouth and tongue "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["keeps his soul from distress. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Mocker is the name of the proud and arrogant man —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of him who acts with excessive pride. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"The craving of the slacker kills him "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because his hands refuse to work. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"All day long he covets more, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the righteous give without restraint. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"The sacrifice of the wicked is detestable— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["how much more so when brought with ill intent! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"A lying witness will perish, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the man who listens to truth will speak forever. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"A wicked man hardens his face, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>puts up a bold front</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the upright man  makes his way sure. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"There is no wisdom, no understanding, no counsel "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that can prevail against the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"A horse is prepared for the day of battle, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but victory is of the LORD. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Good Name"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"A good name is more desirable than great riches; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["favor is better than silver and gold. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The rich and the poor have this in common: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The LORD is Maker of them all. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The prudent see danger and take cover, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the simple keep going and suffer the consequences. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The rewards of humility and the fear of the LORD "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["are wealth and honor and life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Thorns and snares lie on the path of the perverse; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he who guards his soul stays far from them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Train up a child in the way he should go, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and when he is old he will not depart from it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The rich rule over the poor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the borrower  is slave to the lender. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"He who sows injustice will reap disaster , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the rod of his fury will be destroyed. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX includes <i>God blesses a cheerful and generous man, but foolish works will come to an end</i>; see also 2 Corinthians 9:7."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"A generous man   ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>He whose eye is good</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"will be blessed, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for he shares his bread with the poor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Drive out the mocker, and conflict will depart; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even quarreling and insults will cease. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"He who loves a pure heart  and gracious lips "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will have the king for a friend. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The LORD’s eyes keep watch over knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but He frustrates the words of the faithless. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"The slacker says, There is a lion outside! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will be slain in the streets! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The mouth of an adulteress is a deep pit; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he who is under the wrath of the LORD will fall into it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Foolishness is bound up in the heart of a child, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the rod of discipline drives it far from him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Oppressing the poor to enrich oneself or giving gifts to the rich "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will surely lead to poverty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Thirty Sayings of the Wise<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 1"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Incline your ear and hear the words of the wise —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["apply your mind to my knowledge —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"for it is pleasing when you keep them within you  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and they are constantly on your lips. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"So that your trust may be in the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I instruct you today —  yes, you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Have I not written for you thirty sayings ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>written for you excellent sayings</i> or <i>written for you three times</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["about counsel and knowledge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"to show you true and reliable words, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that you may soundly answer those who sent you? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 2"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Do not rob a poor man because he is poor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not crush the afflicted at the gate, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"for the LORD will take up their case "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and will plunder  those who rob them . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 3"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Do not make friends with an angry man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not associate with a hot-tempered man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"or you may learn his ways "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and entangle yourself in a snare. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 4"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Do not be one who gives pledges , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who puts up security for debts. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"If you have nothing with which to pay, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["why should your bed be taken from under you? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 5"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Do not move an ancient boundary stone "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["which your fathers have placed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 6"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Do you see a man skilled in his work? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will be stationed in the presence of kings; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he will not stand before obscure men. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>True Riches"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../1_timothy/6.htm#17|>1 Timothy 6:17–19</a>; <a href =|../james/5.htm|>James 5:1–6</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"When you sit down to dine with a ruler, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["consider carefully   what is set before you, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>who is before you</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and put a knife to your throat "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["if you possess a great appetite. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Do not crave his delicacies, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for that food is deceptive. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 8"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Do not wear yourself out to get rich; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["be wise enough to restrain yourself. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"When you glance  at wealth, it disappears, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for it makes  wings for itself "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and flies like an eagle to the sky. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 9"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Do not eat  the bread of a stingy man , ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>of him whose eye is evil</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not crave his delicacies; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"for  he is keeping track, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["inwardly counting the cost . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>for as he calculates in his soul, so is he</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Eat and drink, he says to you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but his heart is not with you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"You will vomit up what little you have eaten "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and waste your pleasant words. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 10"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," Do not speak to a fool, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for he will despise the wisdom of your words. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 11"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Do not move an ancient boundary stone "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or encroach on the fields of the fatherless, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"for their Redeemer is strong; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will take up  their case against you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 12"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Apply your heart to instruction "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your ears to words of knowledge. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 13"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Do not withhold discipline from a child; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["although you strike him with a rod, he will not die. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}," Strike him with a rod, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and you will deliver his soul from Sheol. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 14"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"My son, if your heart is wise, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["my own heart will indeed  rejoice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"My inmost being ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>My kidneys</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"will rejoice "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when your lips speak what is right. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 15"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Do not let your heart envy sinners, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but  always continue  in the fear of the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For surely there is a future, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your hope will not be cut off. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 16"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Listen,  my son, and be wise, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and guide your heart on the right course. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Do not join those who drink too much wine "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or gorge themselves on meat "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For the drunkard and the glutton will come to poverty, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and drowsiness will clothe them in rags. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 17"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Listen to your father who gave you life, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not despise your mother when she is old. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Invest in truth and never sell it— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in wisdom and instruction and understanding. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The father of a righteous man will greatly rejoice , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who fathers a wise son will delight in him . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"May your father and mother be glad, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and may she who gave you birth rejoice! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 18"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"My son, give me your heart "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and let your eyes delight in my ways. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"For a prostitute is a deep pit, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and an adulteress ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>a foreign woman</i> or <i>a wayward wife</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"is a narrow well. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Like a robber  she lies in wait "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and multiplies the faithless among men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 19"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Who has woe? Who has sorrow? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who has contentions? Who has complaints? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who has needless wounds? Who has bloodshot eyes? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Those who linger over wine, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who go to taste mixed drinks. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Do not gaze at wine while it is red, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when it sparkles in the cup  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and goes down smoothly . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"In the end it bites like a snake "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and stings like a viper. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Your eyes will see strange things, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your mind will utter perversities. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"You will be like one sleeping  on the high seas "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or lying on the top of a mast: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"They struck me, but I feel no pain! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They beat me, but I did not know it! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When can I wake up "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to search for another drink? "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Do Not Envy<p class=|indent1stline|><p class=|subhdg|>Saying 20"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Do not envy wicked  men "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or desire their company ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"for their hearts devise violence, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and their lips declare trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 21"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"By wisdom a house is built "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and by understanding it is established; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"through knowledge its rooms are filled "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with every precious and beautiful treasure. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 22"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"A wise man is strong, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX <i>The wise are mightier than the strong</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a man of knowledge enhances his strength. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Only with sound guidance should you wage war, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and victory lies in a multitude of counselors. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 23"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Wisdom is too high for a fool; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he does not open his mouth in the meeting place. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 24"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"He who plots evil "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will be called a schemer . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"A foolish scheme is sin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a mocker is detestable to men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 25"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"If you faint in the day of distress, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["how small is your strength! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Rescue those being led away to death, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and restrain those stumbling toward the slaughter . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"If you say, Behold, we did not know about this, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["does not He who weighs hearts consider it? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Does not the One who guards your life know? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Will He not repay a man according to his deeds? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 26"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Eat honey, my son, for it is good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the honeycomb is sweet to your taste. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Know therefore that wisdom is sweet to your soul. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["If you find it, there is a future for you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your hope will never be cut off. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 27"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Do not lie in wait, O wicked man, near the dwelling of the righteous; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not destroy his resting place. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"For though a righteous man may fall seven times, he still gets up; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the wicked stumble in bad times. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 28"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Do not gloat when your enemy falls, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not let your heart rejoice when he stumbles, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"or the LORD will see and disapprove , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and turn His wrath away from him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 29"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Do not fret over evildoers, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not be envious of the wicked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"For the evil man has no future; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the lamp of the wicked will be extinguished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|subhdg|>Saying 30"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"My son, fear the LORD and the king, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not associate with the rebellious . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"For they will bring sudden destruction. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who knows what ruin they can bring? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Further Sayings of the Wise"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"These also are sayings of the wise: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["To show partiality  in judgment "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is not good. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Whoever tells the guilty, You are innocent”— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["peoples will curse him, and nations will denounce him; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"but it will go well with those who convict the guilty, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and rich blessing will come upon them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"An honest answer given "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is like a kiss on the lips. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Complete your outdoor work and prepare your field "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["after that, you may build your house. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Do not testify  against your neighbor without cause, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not deceive with your lips. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Do not say, I will do to him  as he has done to me; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will repay the man according to his work. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"I went past the field of a slacker  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and by the vineyard of a man lacking judgment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"}," Thorns had grown up everywhere, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["thistles had covered the ground, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the stone wall was broken down. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"I observed and took it to heart; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I looked and received instruction: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"A little sleep, a little slumber, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a little folding of the hands to rest, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"and poverty will come upon you like a robber, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and need like a bandit . "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"25"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>More Proverbs of Solomon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"These are additional proverbs of Solomon, which were copied by the men of Hezekiah king of Judah: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"It is the glory of God to conceal a matter "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the glory of kings to search it out . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"As the heavens are high and the earth is deep, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so the hearts of kings cannot be searched. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Remove the dross from the silver, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a vessel for a silversmith will come forth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Remove the wicked from the king’s presence, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and his throne will be established in righteousness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Do not exalt yourself in the presence of the king, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not stand in the place of great men; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"for it is better that he says to you, Come up here! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than that you should be demoted in the presence of the prince. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Even what ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Even the one</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"you have seen with your own eyes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"do not bring hastily to court. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Otherwise, what will you do in the end "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when your neighbor puts you to shame ? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Argue your case with your neighbor "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["without betraying another’s confidence, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"lest the one who hears may disgrace you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your infamy never go away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"A word  fitly spoken "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is like apples of gold in settings of silver. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Like an earring of gold or an ornament of fine gold "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a wise man’s rebuke to a listening ear. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Like the cold of snow in the time of harvest "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a trustworthy messenger to those who send him; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he refreshes the soul of his masters. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Like clouds and wind without rain "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is the man who boasts of gifts never given. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Through patience  a ruler can be persuaded, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a gentle tongue can break a bone. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"If you find honey, eat just what you need, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["lest you have too much and vomit it up. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Seldom set foot in your neighbor’s house, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["lest he grow weary and hate you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Like a club or sword or sharp arrow "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a man who bears false witness against his neighbor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Like a broken tooth or a foot out of joint "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is confidence in a faithless man in time of trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Like one who removes a garment on a cold day "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or vinegar poured on a wound ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>on soda</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is one who sings songs to a heavy heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"If your enemy is hungry, give him food to eat, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and if he is thirsty, give him water to drink. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"For in so doing, you will heap burning coals on his head, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX; Hebrew <i>For you will heap burning coals on his head</i>; cited in Romans 12:20"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the LORD will reward you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"As the north wind brings forth rain, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so a backbiting tongue brings angry looks. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Better to live on a corner of the roof "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than to share a house with a quarrelsome wife. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Like cold water to a weary soul "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is good news from a distant land. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Like a muddied spring or a polluted well "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a righteous man who gives way to the wicked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"It is not good to eat too much honey "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or to search out one’s own glory . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Like a city whose walls are broken down "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a man who  does not control his temper. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"26"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Similitudes and Instructions"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Like snow in summer and rain at harvest,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["honor does not befit a fool. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Like a fluttering sparrow or darting  swallow, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["an undeserved curse does not come to rest. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A whip for the horse, a bridle for the donkey, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a rod for the backs of fools! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Do not answer a fool according to his folly, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or you yourself will be like him  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Answer a fool according to his folly, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["lest he become wise in his own eyes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Like cutting off one’s own feet or drinking violence "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is the sending of a message by the hand of a fool. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Like lame legs hanging limp "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a proverb in the mouth of a fool. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Like binding a stone into a sling "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is the giving of honor to a fool. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Like a thorn that goes into the hand of a drunkard "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a proverb in the mouth of a fool. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Like an archer who wounds at random "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is he who hires a fool or passerby. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"As a dog returns to its vomit, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in 2 Peter 2:22"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so a fool repeats his folly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Do you see a man who is wise in his own eyes? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["There is more hope for a fool than for him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"The slacker says, A lion is in the road! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["A fierce lion roams the public square! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"As a door turns on its hinges, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so the slacker turns on his bed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The slacker buries his hand in the dish; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it wearies him to bring it back to his mouth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The slacker is wiser in his own eyes "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than seven men who answer discreetly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Like one who grabs a dog by the ears "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a passerby who meddles in a quarrel not his own. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Like a madman shooting firebrands "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and deadly arrows, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"so is the man who deceives  his neighbor "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and says, I was only joking! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Without wood, a fire goes out; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["without gossip, a conflict ceases. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Like charcoal for embers and wood for fire, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so is a quarrelsome man for kindling strife. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The words of a gossip are like choice morsels "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that go down into the inmost being . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Like glaze  covering  an earthen vessel "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["are burning ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; LXX <i>smooth</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"lips and a wicked heart. ",{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<p class=|indent1|>"]},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"A hateful man disguises himself with his speech, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he lays up deceit in his heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"When he speaks graciously, do not believe him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for seven abominations fill his heart. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Though his hatred is concealed by deception, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["his wickedness will be exposed in the assembly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"He who digs a pit will fall into it, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who rolls a stone will have it roll back on him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"A lying tongue hates those it crushes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a flattering mouth causes ruin. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"27"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Do Not Boast about Tomorrow"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../james/4.htm#13|>James 4:13–17</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Do not boast about tomorrow , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you do not know what a day may bring. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Let another praise you, and not your own mouth— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a stranger, and not your own lips. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A stone is heavy and sand is a burden, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but aggravation from a fool outweighs them both. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Wrath is cruel and anger is like a flood, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but who can withstand  jealousy? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Better an open rebuke "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than love that is concealed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"The wounds of a friend are faithful, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the kisses of an enemy are deceitful. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The soul that is full loathes honey, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but to a hungry soul, any bitter thing is sweet. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Like a bird that strays from its nest "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" is a man who wanders from his home. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Oil and incense bring joy to the heart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the counsel of a friend is sweetness to the soul. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Do not forsake your friend or your father’s friend, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not go to your brother’s house "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the day of your calamity; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["better a neighbor nearby "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than a brother far away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Be wise, my son, and bring joy to my heart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so that I can answer  him who taunts me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The prudent see danger and take cover, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the simple keep going and pay the penalty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Take the garment of him who posts security for a stranger; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["get collateral if it is for a foreigner. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>a wayward woman</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"If one blesses his neighbor with a loud voice early in the morning, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it will be counted to him as a curse. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"A constant dripping on a rainy day "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a contentious woman are alike —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"restraining her is like holding back the wind "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or grasping oil with one’s right hand. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"As iron sharpens iron, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so one man sharpens  another. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>sharpens the face of another</i> or <i>sharpens the countenance of a friend</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Whoever tends a fig tree will eat its fruit, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he who looks after his master will be honored. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"As water reflects the face , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so the heart reflects the true man . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Sheol and Abaddon ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Death and Destruction</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"are never satisfied; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so the eyes of man are never satisfied. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"A crucible for silver and a furnace for gold, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man is tested by the praise accorded him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Though you grind  a fool like grain with mortar and a pestle, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["yet his folly will not depart from him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Be sure to know  the state of your flocks, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and pay close attention  to your herds; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"for riches are not forever, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["nor does a crown endure to every generation. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"When hay is removed and new growth appears "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the grass from the hills is gathered, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"the lambs will provide you with clothing, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the goats with the price of a field. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"You will have plenty of goats’ milk to feed you— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["food for your household "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and nourishment for your maidservants. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"28"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Boldness of the Righteous"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"The wicked flee when no one pursues, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the righteous are as bold as a lion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"A land in rebellion has many rulers, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man of understanding and knowledge  maintains order. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A destitute leader who oppresses the poor "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is like a driving rain that leaves no food. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Those who forsake the law praise the wicked, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but those who keep the law resist them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Evil men do not understand justice, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but those who seek the LORD comprehend fully. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Better a poor man who walks with integrity "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than a rich man whose ways  are perverse. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"A discerning son keeps the law, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a companion of gluttons disgraces his father. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"He who increases his wealth by interest and usury "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["lays it up for one who is kind to the poor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Whoever turns his ear away from hearing the law, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even his prayer is detestable. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"He who leads the upright along the path of evil will fall into his own pit, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the blameless will inherit what is good. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"A rich man is wise in his own eyes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a poor man with discernment sees through him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"When the righteous triumph, there is great glory, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but when the wicked rise, men hide themselves. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"He who conceals his sins will not prosper, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever confesses and renounces them will find mercy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Blessed is the man who is always reverent, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>always fears the LORD</i>; Hebrew does not include <i>the LORD</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who hardens his heart falls into trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Like a roaring lion or a charging bear "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a wicked ruler over a helpless people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"A leader who lacks judgment is also a great oppressor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who hates dishonest profit will prolong his days. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"A man burdened by bloodguilt  will flee into the Pit; ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>will be a fugitive until death</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["let no one support him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"He who walks with integrity will be kept safe, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever is perverse in his ways will suddenly fall. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The one who works his land will have plenty of food, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever chases fantasies will have his fill of poverty. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"A faithful man will abound with blessings, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but one eager to be rich will not go unpunished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"To show partiality  is not good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["yet a man will do wrong for a piece of bread. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"A stingy  man ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>A man whose eye is evil</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"hastens after wealth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and does not know that poverty awaits him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"He who rebukes a man will later find more favor "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["than one who flatters with his tongue. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"He who robs his father or mother, saying, It is not wrong, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["is a companion  to the man who destroys. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"A greedy man  stirs up strife, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who trusts in the LORD will prosper. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"He who trusts in himself  is a fool, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but one who walks in wisdom  will be safe. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Whoever gives to the poor will not be in need, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but he who hides his eyes will receive many curses. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"When the wicked come to power, people hide themselves; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but when they perish, the righteous flourish. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"29"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Flourishing of the Righteous"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"A man who remains stiff-necked  after much reproof "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will suddenly be shattered  beyond recovery. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"When the righteous flourish, the people rejoice, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but when the wicked rule, the people groan. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A man who loves wisdom brings joy to his father, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a companion of prostitutes squanders his wealth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"By justice a king brings stability to the land, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man who exacts tribute ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["29:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>who taxes heavily</i> or <i>who takes bribes</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"demolishes it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"A man who flatters his neighbor "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["spreads  a net for his feet. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"An evil man is caught by his own sin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a righteous one sings and rejoices. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The righteous consider the cause of the poor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the wicked have no regard for such concerns. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Mockers  inflame a city, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the wise turn away anger. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"If a wise man goes to court with  a fool, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["there will be raving and laughing with no resolution. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Men of bloodshed hate a blameless man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the upright care for his life. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["29:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>but the upright seek his soul</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"A fool vents all his anger, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a wise man holds it back. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"If a ruler listens to lies , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["all his officials will be wicked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"The poor man and the oppressor  have this in common: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The LORD gives light to the eyes of both. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"A king who judges the poor with fairness— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["his throne will be established forever. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"A rod of correction imparts wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a child left to himself disgraces his mother. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"When the wicked thrive, rebellion increases; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but the righteous will see their downfall. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Discipline your son, and he will give you rest; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he will bring delight to your soul. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Where there is no vision, the people cast off restraint; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but blessed is he who keeps the Law. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"A servant cannot be corrected by words alone; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["though he understands, he will not respond. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Do you see a man who speaks in haste? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["There is more hope for a fool than for him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"A servant pampered from his youth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will bring grief in the end. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"An angry man stirs up dissension, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a hot-tempered man abounds in transgression. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"A man’s pride will bring him low, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a humble spirit will obtain honor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"A partner to a thief hates his own soul; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["he receives the oath but does not testify. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"The fear of man is a snare, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but whoever trusts in the LORD is set securely on high. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Many seek the ruler’s favor, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a man receives justice from the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"An unjust man is detestable to the righteous, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and one whose way is upright is detestable to the wicked. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"30"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Words of Agur"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"These are the words of Agur son of Jakeh —  the burden that this man declared to Ithiel: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I am weary, O God, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and worn out. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["30:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>declared to Ithiel: “I am weary, O God, but I can prevail.</i> (revocalizations); Hebrew <i>declared to Ithiel—to Ithiel and Ucal:</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Surely I am the most ignorant of men, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and I lack the understanding of a man "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"I have not learned wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and I have no knowledge  of the Holy One. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Who has ascended to heaven and come down? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who has gathered the wind in His hands? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who has bound up the waters in His cloak? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who has established all the ends of the earth? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What is His name, and what is the name of His Son— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["surely you know! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Every word of God is flawless; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He is a shield to those who take refuge in Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Do not add to His words, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["lest He rebuke you and prove you a liar. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Two things I ask  of You —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not refuse me before I die: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Keep falsehood and deceitful words far from me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Give me neither poverty nor riches; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["feed me with the bread that is my portion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Otherwise, I may have too much "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and deny You, saying, Who is the LORD? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Or I may become poor and steal, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["profaning the name of my God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Do not slander a servant to his master, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or he will curse you, and you will bear the guilt. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"There is a generation of those who curse  their fathers "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and do not bless their mothers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"There is a generation of those who are pure in their own eyes "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" and yet unwashed of their filth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"There is a generation— how haughty are their eyes "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and pretentious are their glances —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"there is a generation whose teeth are swords "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and whose jaws are knives, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["devouring the oppressed from the earth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the needy from among men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The leech has two daughters: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Give and Give. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["There are three things that are never satisfied, four that never say, Enough!’: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Sheol, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the barren womb, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["land never satisfied with water, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and fire that never says, Enough! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"As for the eye that mocks a father "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and scorns obedience to a mother, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["may the ravens of the valley pluck it out "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and young vultures devour it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"There are three things too wonderful for me, four that I cannot understand: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"the way of an eagle in the sky, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the way of a snake on a rock, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the way of a ship  at sea, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the way of a man with a maiden. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"This is the way of an adulteress : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She eats and wipes her mouth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and says, I have done nothing wrong. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Under three things the earth trembles, under four it cannot  bear up: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," a servant who becomes king, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a fool who is filled with food, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," an unloved woman who marries, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a maidservant who supplants her mistress. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Four things on earth  are small, yet they are exceedingly wise: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"The ants are creatures of little strength, yet they store up their food in the summer; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"the rock badgers ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["30:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the coneys</i> or <i>the hyraxes</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"are creatures of little power, yet they make their homes in the rocks; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"the locusts have no king, yet they all advance in formation; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"and the lizard can be caught in one’s hands, yet it is found in the palaces of kings. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"There are three things that are stately in their stride, and four that are impressive in their walk: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"a lion, mighty among beasts, refusing to retreat before anything; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"a strutting rooster ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" a he-goat; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a king with his army around him. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["30:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>a king against whom there is no rising up</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"If you have foolishly exalted yourself "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or if you have plotted evil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["put your hand over your mouth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"For as the churning of milk yields butter, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the twisting of the nose draws blood, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so the stirring of anger brings forth strife. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"31"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Sayings for King Lemuel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"These are the words of King Lemuel —  the burden that his mother taught him: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"What shall I say, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>What</i> or <i>What are you doing</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"O my son? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What, O son of my womb? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What, O son of my vows? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Do not spend your strength on women "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or your vigor on those who ruin kings. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"It is not for kings, O Lemuel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["it is not for kings to drink wine, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or for rulers to crave strong drink, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"lest they drink and forget what is decreed, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["depriving all the oppressed  of justice. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Give strong drink to one who is perishing, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and wine to the bitter in soul. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Let him drink and forget his poverty, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and remember his misery no more. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Open your mouth for those with no voice, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for the cause of all the dispossessed . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Open your mouth, judge righteously, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and defend the cause of the poor and needy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Virtues of a Noble Woman"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"A wife ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Verses 10–31 are an acrostic poem, each verse beginning with the successive letters of the Hebrew alphabet."]}],"caller":"+"},"of noble character, who can find? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She is far more precious than rubies. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"The heart of her husband trusts in her, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and he lacks nothing of value. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"She brings him good and not harm "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["all the days of her life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"She selects wool and flax "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and works with eager hands. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"She is like the merchant ships, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["bringing her food from afar. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"She rises while it is still night "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to provide food for her household "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and portions for her maidservants. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"She appraises a field and buys it; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from her earnings  she plants a vineyard. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"She girds herself  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>She girds her loins</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"with strength "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and shows that her arms are strong. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"She sees that her gain is good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and her lamp is not extinguished at night. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"She stretches out her hands to the distaff "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and grasps the spindle with her fingers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"She opens her arms to the poor "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and reaches out her hands to the needy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"When it snows, she has no fear for her household, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they are all  clothed in scarlet. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>doubly clothed</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"She makes coverings for her bed; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["her clothing is fine linen and purple. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Her husband is known at the city gates, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["where he sits among the elders of the land. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"She makes linen garments and sells them; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she delivers sashes to the merchants. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Strength and honor are her clothing, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and she can laugh at the days to come. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"She opens her mouth with wisdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and faithful instruction is on her tongue. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"She watches over the affairs of her household "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and does not eat the bread of idleness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Her children rise up and call her blessed; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["her husband praises her as well: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Many daughters have done noble things, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but you surpass them all! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Charm is deceptive and beauty is fleeting, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but a woman who fears the LORD  is to be praised. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Give her the fruit of her hands, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and let her works praise her at the gates. "]}]}